text: The following lists events that happened during 1993 in Uganda. ==Incumbents== *President: Yoweri Museveni *Vice President: Samson Kisekka *Prime Minister: George Cosmas Adyebo ==Events== *date unknown **Kibale Forest becomes a national park. **NACWOLA (National Community of Women Living with HIV/AIDS) is founded by Beatrice Were. ==Births== * January 1 - Alengot Oromait, Ugandan politician ==References== Category:1990s in Uganda Category:Years of the 20th century in Uganda Uganda Uganda
title: 1993 in Uganda
